Turing Test and CAPTCHA — Architecture Design

This part is conceptual. You don’t need heavy coding — they want system architecture.

(A) Turing Test Implementation
Goal

Determine whether the interacting entity is human or AI.

Architecture
        +--------------------+
        |   Human Judge      |
        +---------+----------+
                  |
                  v
         +------------------+
         | Conversation     |
         | Interface (Chat) |
         +---------+--------+
                   |
          +--------+--------+
          |                 |
          v                 v
   +-------------+   +--------------+
   | Human User  |   | AI Agent     |
   +-------------+   +--------------+

Judge does not know which is which
Components

User Interface

Chat interface.

Conversation Manager

Routes messages to participants.

AI Agent

Generates responses.

Human Participant

Judge Module

Evaluates responses and decides.

Working

Judge asks questions.

Both AI and human respond.

Judge evaluates answers.

If judge cannot reliably distinguish, AI passes the Turing Test.

